BOSTON COLLEGE FOOTBALL MEDIA CONFERENCE
September 9, 2017
Anthony Brown
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT








Wake Forest - 34, Boston College - 10
Q. (No microphone).
ANTHONY BROWN: I Still have confidence in myself.  I've just got to put my teammates in a better position to win.
Q. (No microphone).
ANTHONY BROWN: Better ball placement.  Create YAC yards.  Not really much I can do about that.  Just put the ball in a better spot.
Q. (No microphone).
ANTHONY BROWN: Getting better ball placement.  Just got to put my teammates in better positions to score and the team will have a chance.
Q. (No microphone).
ANTHONY BROWN: Charlie, Sweeney, all our older guys came to me, tried to tell me to keep going, don't worry about it.  Just keep going.  Don't worry about it.  Next play.
Q. Anthony, two questions.  The first is, those first couple of possessions of the game, you guys started with pretty good field position.  What made it so difficult to put a drive together and put points on the board?
ANTHONY BROWN: I don't know right now.  Just going to have to look at the film to see later on tonight.
Q. And secondly, being in a leadership position, what's your message to the team going to be moving forward this week?
ANTHONY BROWN: We just have to go.  I have to get better.  I have to put my teammates in the best position possible to get it done.  So just going to keep going.
Q. Did you feel like you were getting some traction in the opening drive of the third quarter, opened up with the big run?
ANTHONY BROWN: It was a great drive.  We just had to finish it.  Got to get better at that.
Q. (No microphone).
ANTHONY BROWN: Nothing that we haven't seen in practice.  Just got to make better decisions.
Q. (No microphone).






